<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> ride on the pig’s back • ride on the sheep’s back</xh5><p> <i>ride on the pig’s back</i>—(coll.) experience a period of success; enjoy extreme good fortune: The self-employed are leaving the country.... If the place is such a goldmine why do they not stay and continue <u>riding on the pig’s back</u>?</p><p> <i>ride on the sheep’s back</i>—(Austral. sl.) used pertaining to the success of the Australian sheep industry <i>(a pun on the former expression): </i>After <u>riding on the sheep’s back</u>, will Australia end up exporting our ideas and knowledge to the world?</p> </entry>
